message.content:
cs.MOBILE, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.OS, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.MOBILE is the most likely category as the paper is about sharing I/O devices between mobile systems and presents an implementation on Android.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper deals with sharing I/O devices between multiple systems.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses network throughput limitations for camera sharing.
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is relevant as the paper presents a system solution for I/O sharing.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper presents a system-level solution for sharing I/O devices.
